
## Official MCP Documentation and Resources

### Primary Official Documentation

**Official MCP Documentation Site:**
- https://modelcontextprotocol.io/ - The main documentation portal

**Anthropic's MCP Announcement:**
- https://www.anthropic.com/news/model-context-protocol - Official announcement and overview

**Official GitHub Repository:**
- https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol/modelcontextprotocol - Specification and documentation source
- https://github.com/modelcontextprotocol - Main GitHub organization with SDKs and examples

**Anthropic Course:**
- https://anthropic.skilljar.com/introduction-to-model-context-protocol - Official training course

### Key Learning Resources

**Comprehensive Guides:**
- https://www.keywordsai.co/blog/introduction-to-mcp - Complete guide to MCP (2025)
- https://www.descope.com/learn/post/mcp - Detailed explanation of how MCP works
- https://medium.com/@amanatulla1606/anthropics-model-context-protocol-mcp-a-deep-dive-for-developers-1d3db39c9fdc - Developer deep dive

**Reference Information:**
- https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Model_Context_Protocol - Wikipedia overview

### Key Concepts

MCP is an open-source standard for connecting AI applications to external systems, allowing AI applications like Claude to connect to data sources, tools, and workflows. The protocol has three core primitives: tools, resources, and prompts.